  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2019-09-24",
    "date": "2021-03-25T17:08:38Z",
    "text": "Securing Energy Critical Elements and American Jobs Act of 2019\n\nThis bill directs the Department of Energy (DOE) to implement a program to assure the long-term, secure, and sustainable supply of energy critical elements to satisfy the national security, economic well-being, and industrial production needs of the United States.\n\nSpecifically, the bill\n\n promotes collaboration in the program to include opportunities for students and staff at institutions of higher education and international collaboration; requires DOE to develop and update a plan every two years for how it intends to carry out the program; and creates a Critical Materials Information Center to collect, catalogue, disseminate, and archive information that is generated by research and development activities under the program."
  },
